The '''Asian V8 Championship Series''' (AV8C) was a [[motorsports]] competition for [[Stock car racing|stock car race drivers]] from the [[Asia-Pacific]]. The only edition of the racing series took place in 2014, over two events at the [[Clark International Speedway]] in [[Pampanga]] and the [[Batangas Racing Circuit]] in [[Batangas]], both in the [[Philippines]]. The tournament was organized by the Philippine Formula Autosports Foundation and was intended to set the Philippines as a hub for [[NASCAR]] racing in Asia. The overall winner of the tournament will compete at the [[NASCAR Whelen Euro Series|NASCAR Whelen Series]] and in the K&N Pro NASCAR Series. <ref>http://www.carguide.ph/2014/02/nascar-comes-to-philippines-via-asian.html</ref><ref>http://motioncars.inquirer.net/26241/16-intl-drivers-8-nascar-cars-set-to-race-in-ph</ref>
